WorkEffort.description: This Index will measure on a monthly basis the extent to which EFSA is effective in meeting the target of the number of outputs as planned in the work programme. This deals with outputs of the scientific work (scientific outputs and reports) as well as with communication outputs of DEMO.

This index will measure on a monthly basis the extent to which the work currently performed at EFSA is running according to schedule. It will indicate for work in progress on applications, generic requests, grants and procurement and communication activities the extent to which this work is expected to be finalised within the predefined deadlines. The index will help the organization to identify potential risks of not meeting the deadlines sufficiently in advance to take corrective action where possible.

This index will measure on a monthly basis the extent to which EFSA is being effective in spending its financial resources according to plan. It will look at the commitments and payments as well as at the proportion of budget transfers.

This index provides information on the extent to which EFSA's internal processes are run according to the quality standards. As supporting processes are currently not mapped and their implementation is not monitored, this index deals with aspects of the science processes, such as the DOI requirement, activities in various stages of the RAW process and timely publishing of meetings and agendas prior to meetings.

This index provides information on the efficiency of the performance of EFSA's processes. As the supporting processes are currently not mapped nor monitored, it is suggested to monitor certain aspects that affect the efficiency of (part of) the scientific process at this stage.
This index measures the extent to which EFSA's outputs are delivered "on time", meaning by the predefined deadline.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of scientific outputs to date Vs planned Year to date (following work in Panels and WG)
WorkEffort.description: This indicator will demonstrate EFSA's effectiveness in meeting the target of number of scientific outputs as defined in the work programme. It compares the actual number of scientific outputs produced year to date with the target of scientific outputs year to date. The effectiveness score of each type of scientific output is weighted in function of its share in the total number of outputs planned for the year. The weight has been calculated based on the figures of scientific outputs produced as reported in the AAR 2010.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of communications activities to date Vs planned year to date
WorkEffort.description: This indicator will demonstrate EFSA's effectiveness in meeting the target of number of communication outputs as defined in the work programme. It compares the actual number of communication outputs produced year to date with the target of communication outputs year to date. The effectiveness score of each type of communication output is weighted in function of its share in the total number of outputs planned for the year. The weight has been calculated based on the figures of communication outputs produced as reported in the MP 2012.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of supporting publications published Vs total reports planned
WorkEffort.description: This indicator will demonstrate EFSA's effectiveness in meeting the target of number of reports as defined in the work programme. It compares the actual number of reports produced year to date with the target of number of reports year to date. The effectiveness score of each type of report is weighted in function of its share in the total number of reports planned for the year. The weight has been calculated based on the numbers of reports produced as reported in the AAR 2010.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of applications on track Vs total application currently worked on
WorkEffort.description: This indicator will measure on a monthly basis the extent to which the work performed at EFSA on the applications is expected to be finalised within the predefined deadlines. In a first phase, the indicator will be based upon self-assessment of the units performing the work concerned. It is however suggested that in a next phase the assessment of whether the work in progress will be finalized within the predefined deadlines will be based on information from a progress tracking system.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of communications activities on outputs on track Vs total currently worked on
WorkEffort.description: This indicator will measure on a monthly basis the extent to which the work performed at EFSA on communication activities is expected to be finalised within the predefined deadlines. In a first phase, the indicator will be based upon self-assessment of the units performing the work concerned. It is however suggested that in a next phase the assessment of whether the work in progress will be finalized within the predefined deadlines will be based on information from a progress tracking system.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Global commitment rate versus global target
WorkEffort.description: This demonstrates overall timeliness of the budget execution. This indicator will give the detail per budget title and Directorate as well. Budget titles: -staff -infrastructure -operations This demonstrates overall budget effectiveness of the main operational “tools” utilized by EFSA to conduct its mission.
This indicator will give the detail commitment per topics.
This indicator will give the detail payments per topics.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of Mandates where all steps of RAW process completed on time Vs total number of Mandates accepted
WorkEffort.description: Checks that the various stages of the RAW Process are completed within the predefined/agreed timeframes.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of questions completed more than 10% of time before the required deadline Vs total number of questions
WorkEffort.description: Measures the percentage of mandates completed 10 % ahead of the planned deadline Vs the total number of mandates received within the same timeframe.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of Applications for regulated products adopted on time Vs total number adopted
WorkEffort.description: Measures the number of Mandates requiring modification by EFSA before work can start on them as a percentage of the total number of mandates received. This demonstrates the performance in relation to EFSA's core value of timeliness to adopt opinions concerning regulated substances or products against agreed timelines which have been agreed with the European Commission and/or established in legislation. The timeliness score of this type of scientific output adopted in relation to regulated products is weighted in function of its share in contributing to the overall timeliness of the outputs for the year.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of Scientific outputs adopted on time Vs total number adopted
WorkEffort.description: This demonstrates the performance of EFSA in relation to the number of ‘generic' opinions adopted on time which do not directly relate to a specific regulated substance or product but include guidance documents which do relate to such products. The timeliness score of this type of scientific output adopted in relation to generic opinions adopted is weighted in function of its share in contributing to the overall timeliness of the outputs for the year.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of outputs published (without press release/web story) on time Vs total number published (other and supported publications)
WorkEffort.description: This demonstrates performance in relation to EFSA's core value of timeliness to plan manage and deliver projects within agreed timelines. The timeliness score of this type of scientific output published on time is weighted in function of its share in contributing to the overall timeliness of the outputs for the year.

WorkEffort.workEffortName: Number of outputs accompanied by a press release/web story published on time Vs total number published
WorkEffort.description: This demonstrates performance in relation to EFSA's core value of timeliness to plan manage and deliver projects within agreed timelines when communication activities are linked to the publication of a scientific output.
